urrent density. In a plasma that remains close to a global magnetic\nequilibrium, this can reflect bulk displacement or motion of the plasma. This\nbuild-up signature to an intrinsic ELM can be extracted from a time interval of\ndata that does not extend beyond the ELM occurrence time, so that these full\nflux loop signals could assist in ELM prediction or mitigation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Mar 2015 10:02:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-24"}
